\displaystyle\int{\dfrac{\sin x}{1+\sin x}}dx
\frac{\sin x}{1+ \sin x} = \frac{\sin x(1 - \sin x)}{(1+\sin x)(1 - \sin x)} = \frac{\sin x - (\sin x)^2}{1 - (\sin x)^2} = \frac{\sin x - (\sin x)^2}{(\cos x)^2} \\= \frac{\sin x}{(\cos x)^2} - (\tan x)^2
\frac{\sin{x}}{1+\sin{x}}
\frac{\sin{x}}{1+\sin{x}}= \frac{1+\sin{x}-1}{1+\sin{x}} =1 -\frac{1}{1+\sin{x}} 
u=\tan{\frac{x}{2}}
\int dx - \int\frac{2}{u^2+2u+1}\,du 
